## Technical Writing Tips

- Use active voice when possible
- Keep paragraphs short (3-4 sentences maximum)
- Include bulleted or numbered lists for easy scanning
- Use transition words to guide readers through the content
- Break up text with subheadings every 300-400 words
- Bold important information for emphasis
- Link to related content using descriptive anchor text
- Use specific examples to illustrate abstract concepts
- Include statistics and data points when available
- Address potential questions or objections within the content

## Avoiding Common Content Issues

- Don't make unsubstantiated claims
- Avoid overly promotional language
- Don't use jargon without explanation
- Avoid overgeneralizing regional or local issues
- Don't make guarantees about contractor quality or pricing
- Avoid vague advice ("hire a professional" without context)
- Don't present opinions as facts
- Avoid dated or potentially inaccurate statistics

When creating content for any service category, adapt these guidelines to the specific service while maintaining the consistent structure and quality standards defined here.